<div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />IMO, tile editing programs are too limited, and because everything has to be drawn in little boxes the graphics don't even look very good in the end.<br /></div><br />In YY-CHR the whole 128x128 pixel bank can be drawn to by changing the zoom to 1x.<br /><br />Personally I prefer Photoshop though, and custom tools for converting (lot of duplication of work going around, eh?). One thing that YY-CHR is missing is the ability to optimize redundant tiles.<br /><br />This tool by Shiru is good for making nametables: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=7237">http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=7237</a><!-- m --><br /><br />What I really *want* is tools to completely take away the need to deal with any of these technicalities. You'd just give a bunch of image files (bg tiles, sprite anim frames) to a tool, specify which bank you want them in and it would generate the necessary files and possibly some assembler equities (letting the programmer know where the tiles were placed or something like that, if necessary). But like always, designing a tool that is general enough is not an easy task.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">thefox</a> — Wed Feb 02, 2011 2:41 am</p><hr />
